Scenario Analysis
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Further Development
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This paper has outlined the main design and market mechanism for the structure.
 Further study is still requred for below aspects.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Base Rate Discovery
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Arbitrary rate can be used for Class A coupon and it will be traded on premiumn
 or at discount based on the market required rate of return, However, it
 is desirable that Class A trades close to its net value, which means the
 coupon rate for Class A should be chosen close to market required rate
 of return.
 Currently there are a few rates in the market, such as USD borrowing cost
 in a few centralized exchanges ranging from 20% to over 40% per annun.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Optimal Reset Threshold and Frequency
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is important to keep leverage for Class B within certain range: not too
 high so as to protect Class A holders from sudden price drop and not too
 low so as to keep Class B attractive to leveraged investors.
 However, it is undesirable that resets happen too frequent.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Other Coin Based Structure
\end_layout

